WEBVTT

00:01.601 --> 00:04.337
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.404 --> 00:11.444
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.278 --> 00:14.647
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.714 --> 00:16.383
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.449 --> 00:18.718
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.785 --> 00:24.391
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.457 --> 00:26.292
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.359 --> 00:29.562
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.664 --> 00:34.601
[sign buzzing]

00:34.667 --> 00:36.236
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:36.302 --> 00:37.837
- [barks]

00:37.904 --> 00:40.073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:40.140 --> 00:43.710
- Wow, my first stay at a hotel.

00:43.777 --> 00:45.612
This is incredible!

00:45.678 --> 00:47.180
[panting]

00:47.247 --> 00:49.115
- Ooh, careful, Harvey!
That door doesn't close.

00:49.182 --> 00:52.485
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

00:52.552 --> 00:55.655
Whoa.

00:55.722 --> 00:57.590
[retches]

00:57.657 --> 00:59.692
I'm okay!

00:59.759 --> 01:02.695
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

01:02.762 --> 01:09.702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:09.769 --> 01:11.671
[ding]

01:11.738 --> 01:15.341
- Hello, we're here to check in
for the library conference.

01:15.408 --> 01:18.144
- Welcome!
So, how many nights

01:18.211 --> 01:19.813
will you be staying with us?

01:19.879 --> 01:22.248
- Long enough for a good nap.

01:22.315 --> 01:23.583
[mumbles]

01:23.650 --> 01:25.285
[snoring]

01:25.351 --> 01:28.755
- Okay...I got the...bags.
[grunts]

01:28.822 --> 01:30.056
[thud]

01:30.123 --> 01:32.692
{\an3}- Oh, thanks, honey.
I'll take those.

01:35.428 --> 01:39.299
- Uh, this motel doesn't have,
like, uh, oh, an exercise room

01:39.365 --> 01:41.100
or anything like that, does it?

01:41.167 --> 01:44.871
- Ooh, you must be talking about
our executive gym.

01:44.938 --> 01:46.539
- Ooh.

01:46.606 --> 01:48.942
- Wow, golf.

01:49.008 --> 01:50.410
- Ooh, mini golf.

01:50.477 --> 01:53.780
{\an1}Probably only half the fun
of full-sized golf.

01:53.847 --> 01:55.715
{\an1}Whoa.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.016
[laughter]

01:57.083 --> 02:00.687
Oh, my gosh, they got a slide!

02:00.753 --> 02:02.689
It looks like so much fun!

02:02.755 --> 02:05.692
I want that to be me.

02:05.758 --> 02:11.898
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:11.965 --> 02:14.234
[splash]

02:14.300 --> 02:16.236
{\an3}- I've always thought
of you as a four,

02:16.302 --> 02:19.005
but now I see you're a full ten!

02:19.072 --> 02:22.108
[cheering]

02:22.175 --> 02:24.344
- Yeah, yeah, that works.

02:24.410 --> 02:28.481
Oh, boy, oh, boy, oh, boy,
oh boy, oh, boy!

02:28.548 --> 02:29.649
{\an1}Huh?

02:29.716 --> 02:31.551
"No kids under 11"?

02:31.618 --> 02:33.987
But--

02:34.053 --> 02:35.555
[splash]

02:35.622 --> 02:37.924
- All right, I should try
to get some work done.

02:37.991 --> 02:39.859
{\an1}- And I'm gonna go nap
in the room.

02:39.926 --> 02:41.561
Don't knock.

02:43.363 --> 02:45.131
- Ugh, it's worse
than I thought.

02:45.198 --> 02:46.633
- Dad, can you take me
down the big slide?

02:46.699 --> 02:47.634
{\an1}- Harvey!

02:47.700 --> 02:48.635
both: Ahh!

02:48.701 --> 02:50.470
- [grunts]

02:50.537 --> 02:53.706
- I'll take you down the slide
right after we go to the gym.

02:54.841 --> 02:57.911
Son, this is gonna be us soon.

02:57.977 --> 03:00.079
- [snoring]

03:00.146 --> 03:02.949
Hey, get out of my room!

03:03.016 --> 03:05.552
- Uh, this is the gym.

03:05.618 --> 03:09.055
- Oh, well, I warmed it up
for you anyway.

03:09.889 --> 03:11.824
- Hmm, 15 is mid-range.

03:11.891 --> 03:14.160
{\an1}[grunting]

03:14.227 --> 03:16.763
Okay, 10 is good too.

03:16.829 --> 03:19.198
- Hah, look, one for each hand!

03:19.265 --> 03:20.967
They're like pom-poms.

03:21.034 --> 03:23.069
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:23.136 --> 03:26.005
Ah, perfect.

03:26.072 --> 03:28.041
- Go, Dad!
Go, Dad!

03:28.107 --> 03:29.676
No pain, no gain!

03:29.742 --> 03:32.345
- Harvey, come on over here
and be my spotter.

03:32.412 --> 03:34.280
- Oh, okay.
[clang]

03:34.347 --> 03:35.882
You can count on me.

03:35.949 --> 03:39.552
- [grunting]

03:39.619 --> 03:41.654
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:41.721 --> 03:43.523
[yells]

03:43.590 --> 03:44.991
One!

03:45.058 --> 03:47.493
[grunting]

03:47.560 --> 03:48.895
[splash]

03:48.962 --> 03:49.896
[laughter]

03:49.963 --> 03:51.130
- Oh, man.

03:51.197 --> 03:54.100
- [grunting]

03:54.167 --> 03:55.468
Two!

03:55.535 --> 03:57.470
{\an1}- All right, let's pick up
the pace here.

03:57.537 --> 03:59.439
How we doing?
- Great.

03:59.505 --> 04:02.008
{\an3}1,000 of these,
and we're good to go.

04:02.075 --> 04:04.978
{\an3}[grunting]

04:05.044 --> 04:06.646
[spluttering]

04:06.713 --> 04:09.382
- Oh, I'll never get down
the slide at this rate.

04:09.449 --> 04:13.319
{\an1}Uh, here, Dad, how about you
just do one big press?

04:13.386 --> 04:15.254
- [grunts]
Harvey!

04:15.321 --> 04:17.390
- Are you feeling the burn?

04:17.457 --> 04:20.226
- [grunts]
I'm feeling it!

04:20.293 --> 04:21.728
I'm feel--
whoa!

04:21.793 --> 04:22.895
[clanging]

04:22.962 --> 04:24.631
- Huh?
Dad?

04:24.697 --> 04:25.932
{\an1}Dad?

04:25.999 --> 04:28.901
{\an3}- Harvey?
Call the number

04:28.968 --> 04:32.271
on my medical anklet.

04:33.272 --> 04:35.675
- There we go.
It's only a couple of bruises.

04:35.742 --> 04:37.176
You'll be fine.

04:37.243 --> 04:39.545
I'm really glad I made him
bring the anklet.

04:39.612 --> 04:41.948
- Can Dad still take me
to the pool later?

04:42.015 --> 04:44.684
- Oh, no, he can't go
anywhere near a pool.

04:44.751 --> 04:46.386
- Aww.
- Aww.

04:46.452 --> 04:48.821
- But I can take you.
- Ahh!

04:48.888 --> 04:51.090
- Right after
my library conference.

04:51.157 --> 04:53.326
- Aww.

04:53.393 --> 04:56.896
{\an1}- Welcome to our annual
library conference.

04:56.963 --> 04:59.232
We're all very excited.

04:59.298 --> 05:00.967
- How long does this last?

05:01.034 --> 05:02.468
- Oh, don't worry, just a few--

05:02.535 --> 05:04.704
- Okay, I guess
I can handle a few--

05:04.771 --> 05:06.139
- Hours.

05:07.340 --> 05:11.477
- Books go on shelves
in alphabetical order.

05:11.544 --> 05:14.580
The alphabet starts
with the letter "A,"

05:14.647 --> 05:17.617
and then the letter "B,"
and then--

05:17.684 --> 05:20.186
- Is he gonna say the entire--?

05:21.954 --> 05:25.892
- And lastly, the letter "Z."

05:25.958 --> 05:27.427
- [groans]

05:27.493 --> 05:30.029
- And, if you forget that,
you only

05:30.096 --> 05:32.665
have your-shelf to blame.

05:32.732 --> 05:35.835
Books and shelves,
and I just thought of that.

05:35.902 --> 05:37.437
- I gotta get out of here.

05:37.503 --> 05:41.040
{\an1}- Now this is called
a label maker.

05:41.107 --> 05:42.642
- Label marker?

05:42.709 --> 05:47.313
- Yeah, it's the ultimate
organizational machine.

05:47.380 --> 05:51.617
Nothing will be
out of place ever again.

05:51.684 --> 05:53.586
Do you have any questions
about that?

05:53.653 --> 05:55.088
- [grunts]

05:55.154 --> 05:57.457
It the adhesive permanent?
[gasps]

05:57.523 --> 06:02.395
- That's a really good question
with a very long answer.

06:02.462 --> 06:03.696
Okay, let me explain.

06:03.763 --> 06:05.898
You see...
- What am I doing?

06:05.965 --> 06:08.134
I'm sabotaging my own pool time.

06:08.201 --> 06:10.837
- 'Cause the subsections
of sections...

06:10.903 --> 06:13.740
[laughter]

06:13.806 --> 06:15.742
- [groans]

06:15.808 --> 06:19.412
- Now these beauties
protect books from dust.

06:19.479 --> 06:21.748
Who here dislikes dust?

06:22.615 --> 06:25.551
- No!
[grunting]

06:25.618 --> 06:27.754
- But do they also
protect from spills?

06:27.820 --> 06:28.921
[gasps]

06:28.988 --> 06:31.424
- Well, it depends on the spill.

06:31.491 --> 06:34.360
If it was, say,
a vanilla milkshake

06:34.427 --> 06:35.795
that's a little bit
of a problem,

06:35.862 --> 06:37.396
but not as much as...
- [gasps]

06:37.463 --> 06:39.198
- A banana milkshake
or a strawberry--

06:39.265 --> 06:40.600
- Michelle?

06:40.666 --> 06:42.602
They're not gonna
let her slide alone.

06:42.668 --> 06:45.071
- Water, that's a no-brainer.

06:45.138 --> 06:49.509
Soda, that could actually
help us get out other stains--

06:49.575 --> 06:51.911
- [yells]
My own sister!

06:51.978 --> 06:53.646
I gotta go down that slide, now!

06:53.713 --> 06:55.448
Sorry, Mom!
Bye, Mom!

06:55.515 --> 06:56.883
- Harvey?
[door slams]

06:56.949 --> 06:58.384
- [snoring]

06:58.451 --> 07:00.253
[knocking]

07:00.319 --> 07:02.989
- Hey, Grandpa.
- [snoring]

07:03.055 --> 07:05.124
- Oh, he's asleep.

07:05.191 --> 07:07.059
{\an1}Well, I wouldn't want
to wake him up.

07:07.126 --> 07:08.561
[clang]

07:08.628 --> 07:10.229
{\an3}- Hmm, huh, what, who,
what, huh--Harvey?

07:10.296 --> 07:11.764
- Oh, good, you're awake.

07:11.831 --> 07:13.800
Can you please take me down
to the big slide?

07:13.866 --> 07:16.402
Mom and Dad don't understand
the word "urgent."

07:16.469 --> 07:19.272
- All right, I'll take you.

07:19.338 --> 07:22.875
- Yes, Grandpa, oh,
I could kiss you!

07:22.942 --> 07:24.143
But I won't.

07:24.210 --> 07:26.512
- I appreciate that.

07:26.579 --> 07:28.614
- Oh, boy, oh, boy,
oh, boy, oh, boy!

07:28.681 --> 07:31.951
Okay, Grandpa, so I think
the line is over there.

07:32.018 --> 07:34.253
Wait, the slide is this way.

07:34.320 --> 07:37.190
{\an1}- Okay, first, we have to
loosen up our pores.

07:37.256 --> 07:39.425
- No, no, no!

07:39.492 --> 07:43.396
[sizzling]

07:43.462 --> 07:47.066
- Ahh, now this is a vacation.

07:47.133 --> 07:50.603
- Uh, are you sure it's healthy
to lose this much fluid?

07:50.670 --> 07:52.605
- Eh, you're young.

07:52.672 --> 07:56.342
Gonna take a long time in here
to make this old man sweat.

07:56.409 --> 07:58.811
- We don't have a long time.

07:58.878 --> 08:01.881
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:01.948 --> 08:05.117
[sizzling]

08:05.184 --> 08:07.520
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:07.587 --> 08:09.422
{\an1}- All right, Grandpa,
you sweating?

08:09.488 --> 08:10.623
{\an1}I'm sweating.
Let's go.

08:10.690 --> 08:12.358
- Ah, ow, the sweat!

08:12.425 --> 08:14.227
Ah, oh, it's getting
in my good eye.

08:14.293 --> 08:18.364
Ugh, ugh, oh, ah.
[grunting]

08:18.431 --> 08:20.633
- Aww.
[giggles]

08:20.700 --> 08:22.168
- Hello.
- No, Harvey,

08:22.235 --> 08:23.836
do not make eye contact, no.

08:23.903 --> 08:26.339
{\an1}- Why?
She's just being friendly.

08:26.405 --> 08:28.241
{\an3}- Friendly's not
what she wants, Harvey.

08:28.307 --> 08:30.409
She--She wants my body.

08:30.476 --> 08:31.944
- Ew, Grandpa.

08:32.010 --> 08:35.715
- Uh, sorry, not interested.
No, thank you.

08:35.780 --> 08:37.650
- [giggles]
Aww.

08:37.717 --> 08:39.418
- Hold on.
Oh, she's coming over here.

08:39.485 --> 08:41.020
{\an3}Harvey, Harvey,
you gotta help me.

08:41.087 --> 08:42.221
I'm not ready for love.

08:42.288 --> 08:44.256
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:44.323 --> 08:45.992
- Ooh?

08:46.058 --> 08:47.226
{\an3}[groans]

08:47.293 --> 08:49.395
both: [panting]

08:49.462 --> 08:51.330
- Whew, okay, Grandpa.

08:51.397 --> 08:53.332
Ready for the slide?

08:53.399 --> 08:54.734
- I can't let her find me.

08:54.800 --> 08:56.068
{\an1}- Grandpa!

08:56.135 --> 08:58.537
Ugh, he's gone.

08:58.604 --> 09:00.640
- That feels good.

09:00.706 --> 09:03.609
{\an1}- Geez, buddy, do you even
have a spine?

09:03.676 --> 09:06.512
{\an1}[grunts]
Uh, oh, oh, no.

09:06.579 --> 09:09.348
Uh-oh, oh, no, no,
no, no, no, oh, no!

09:09.415 --> 09:11.050
- Ahh.

09:11.117 --> 09:12.418
- Jeremy!

09:12.485 --> 09:13.586
- [screams]
- You're my dad now.

09:13.653 --> 09:15.054
There's no time to explain.

09:15.121 --> 09:17.156
- Oh--Okay.

09:17.223 --> 09:20.059
- Excuse me, father and son
coming through here.

09:20.126 --> 09:21.127
- Ow!
- Hey.

09:21.193 --> 09:22.528
- Hah!
- Whoa!

09:22.595 --> 09:26.032
- Yes, yes,
we're finally at the top!

09:26.098 --> 09:28.234
Thank you, Dad!

09:28.301 --> 09:30.469
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:30.536 --> 09:32.905
Whenever you're ready.

09:32.972 --> 09:34.707
Anytime now.

09:34.774 --> 09:37.176
- Yeah, I think I'm stuck.

09:37.243 --> 09:38.844
{\an1}- What?
No!

09:38.911 --> 09:42.915
[grunting]

09:43.916 --> 09:45.418
- Oh, boy.

09:45.484 --> 09:47.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:47.086 --> 09:49.255
{\an1}- Shh, it's gonna be okay,
little boy.

09:49.322 --> 09:52.725
Like, whoa, you are a big child.

09:52.792 --> 09:56.429
- Oh, hey, wait a minute.

09:56.495 --> 09:58.397
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:58.464 --> 10:01.367
I finally made it!

10:01.434 --> 10:03.602
All right, then, here we go!

10:03.669 --> 10:05.204
[whistle tweets]

10:05.271 --> 10:07.073
- All right, pool's closed.

10:10.176 --> 10:11.477
- [laughing

10:11.544 --> 10:12.511
Aww.

10:12.578 --> 10:13.946
[whistle tweets]

10:14.013 --> 10:14.947
[beep]

10:15.014 --> 10:16.215
- Slide's off.

10:16.282 --> 10:19.418
[gurgling]

10:19.485 --> 10:22.088
- No!
No!

10:22.154 --> 10:24.890
- Hey, Harvey,
come on down here, buddy.

10:24.957 --> 10:28.260
You can try the slide
some other time.

10:28.327 --> 10:30.730
- [sighs]
All right.

10:32.498 --> 10:34.967
But what if there isn't
another time?

10:35.034 --> 10:38.738
I know this is way dangerous
and super illegal,

10:38.804 --> 10:41.240
but I've come too far
to stop now.

10:41.307 --> 10:42.708
I'm gonna do it.

10:42.775 --> 10:45.945
I'm gonna be a slider!

10:46.012 --> 10:47.513
<i>[epic music]</i>

10:47.580 --> 10:51.784
[squeaking]

10:55.788 --> 10:58.457
{\an3}Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!
Yeah!

10:58.524 --> 11:02.194
{\an3}I'm sliding!
I'm going so fast!

11:02.261 --> 11:03.329
Do you see this?

11:03.396 --> 11:04.563
[splash]

11:04.630 --> 11:06.432
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:06.499 --> 11:08.534
Did you guys see it?
I did it!

11:08.601 --> 11:10.302
I slid down the slide!

11:10.369 --> 11:11.470
It was awesome!

11:11.537 --> 11:13.839
{\an8}all: [gasp]

11:13.906 --> 11:15.508
{\an8}- What?

11:16.642 --> 11:18.077
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

11:18.144 --> 11:19.345
[knocking]

11:19.412 --> 11:20.579
- Harvey?

11:20.646 --> 11:22.481
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:22.548 --> 11:25.651
Harvey?
Harvey?

11:25.718 --> 11:28.220
Harvey?
Are you in there, buddy?

11:28.287 --> 11:29.688
Harvey?
Harvey?

11:29.755 --> 11:31.323
- Irving, Irving?
- Where are you?

11:31.390 --> 11:33.592
- Are you there, Irving?
- Harvey, Harvey, Harvey?

11:33.659 --> 11:36.228
- Irving, where you?
- Harvey, where are you?

11:36.295 --> 11:38.964
Harvey?

11:39.031 --> 11:41.133
[sniffling]

11:41.200 --> 11:43.936
[sobbing]

11:44.003 --> 11:46.472
[sobbing]
I don't know where he is!

11:46.539 --> 11:48.974
{\an1}[sobbing]
He's gone!

11:49.041 --> 11:50.676
- Hey, will you
take care of that?

11:50.743 --> 11:53.345
{\an1}- [sobbing]
Oh, gosh, he's gone!

11:53.412 --> 11:54.380
[clapping]

11:54.447 --> 11:56.715
{\an3}Hey.
Stop.

11:56.782 --> 12:00.453
{\an1}- No, I won't stop,
because Harvey is gone!

12:00.519 --> 12:03.289
- Dade, he told you--
he's at the library convention

12:03.355 --> 12:04.990
with his family.

12:05.057 --> 12:07.526
I know this is hard for you
to understand in your state,

12:07.593 --> 12:09.161
{\an3}but it's just
for a little while.

12:09.228 --> 12:11.597
{\an3}Harvey'll be back,
just chill out.

12:11.664 --> 12:13.966
{\an1}- Relax.

12:14.033 --> 12:15.201
{\an1}Mwah.

12:15.267 --> 12:19.004
- Trust me--everything's
gonna be fine.

12:19.071 --> 12:20.406
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:20.473 --> 12:23.375
[yelling]

12:23.442 --> 12:30.683
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:33.252 --> 12:36.455
So as you may have noticed,
Harvey's away on a trip.

12:36.522 --> 12:38.991
But it's no big deal--
we can have fun without him!

12:39.058 --> 12:41.327
- Yeah!
- Yeah, okay, I mean, yeah.

12:41.393 --> 12:42.428
- Yeah.
- No big deal.

12:42.495 --> 12:43.963
- Yeah, no big deal.

12:44.029 --> 12:45.631
- I mean, you know,
half my heart is missing,

12:45.698 --> 12:46.866
but, yeah, no big deal.

12:46.932 --> 12:50.202
- I can do this with my foot!

12:50.269 --> 12:51.570
- Nice!

12:51.637 --> 12:52.905
Anyone else have
something to share?

12:52.972 --> 12:54.940
- Um, we could talk
about the weather.

12:55.007 --> 12:56.542
Clear skies, pretty nice.

12:56.609 --> 12:59.078
- I saw a cloud!
- Oh, gosh, you're right.

12:59.145 --> 13:02.548
{\an1}It's probably going to rain.
I'm sorry, I'm sorry!

13:02.615 --> 13:04.884
- I can feel the weather
in me hamstring.

13:05.885 --> 13:08.020
Nope, definitely not raining.

13:08.087 --> 13:10.122
- [sighs]
I miss Harvey.

13:10.189 --> 13:12.758
{\an1}- Kratz, I know you're sad,
but I promise you,

13:12.825 --> 13:16.095
whatever you're feeling,
I feel 100 times worse.

13:16.162 --> 13:19.231
- Ugh, it's only weird
if you guys make it weird.

13:19.298 --> 13:21.700
{\an1}- What would Harvey
want to do if he was here?

13:21.767 --> 13:23.636
{\an3}- He would want to play
a game or something!

13:23.702 --> 13:26.972
- Oh, yeah, let's play the game
he's always talking about!

13:27.039 --> 13:30.843
- "'Fair and Square' is a game
of manners, turn-taking,

13:30.910 --> 13:33.412
and microeconomics."

13:33.479 --> 13:34.780
Okay.

13:34.847 --> 13:36.615
- I'll roll first!

13:36.682 --> 13:38.317
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:38.384 --> 13:40.252
"You vacuum the house
for your mom.

13:40.319 --> 13:41.820
"Collect $5.00.

13:41.887 --> 13:44.557
"Then put it back because
the joy of helping others

13:44.623 --> 13:47.259
is payment enough."
Oh.

13:48.127 --> 13:51.163
{\an1}- Oh, it's like
Harvey's right here.

13:51.230 --> 13:52.531
I have the chills.

13:52.598 --> 13:54.300
- I have bills to pay!

13:54.366 --> 13:59.071
- This game isn't very realistic
because nothing in life is fair

13:59.138 --> 14:00.372
or square.

14:00.439 --> 14:04.443
- Oop, just drew
a "went to bed early" card.

14:04.510 --> 14:07.379
Foo, let's hear the score.

14:07.446 --> 14:08.981
- Huh?
Oh.

14:09.048 --> 14:12.551
The score is...
I don't know.

14:12.618 --> 14:14.019
- All right, this game's dumb.

14:14.086 --> 14:16.021
Maybe we're
looking at this all wrong.

14:16.088 --> 14:18.057
I mean, this is our chance
to do the stuff

14:18.123 --> 14:20.059
that Harvey never wants to do.

14:20.125 --> 14:22.294
Maybe it's a good thing
that he's gone.

14:22.361 --> 14:23.529
- Blasphemy!

14:23.596 --> 14:25.631
How--?
Ahh, ahh!

14:25.698 --> 14:27.600
- Like rough-housing,
for example.

14:27.666 --> 14:28.867
Harvey would hate this.

14:28.934 --> 14:30.769
- Uncle, ahh, uncle!

14:30.836 --> 14:32.238
- She's got a point, you know.

14:32.304 --> 14:34.340
- It wouldn't hurt
to mix things up.

14:34.406 --> 14:38.344
{\an1}- No, no, let's just leave
everything unmixed

14:38.410 --> 14:39.912
until Harvey gets back.

14:39.979 --> 14:41.747
- Let's go play in the mud!

14:41.814 --> 14:43.649
- No, no, no, no, no, no!

14:43.716 --> 14:46.852
Let's just all stay right here
and just sit nice and sit still

14:46.919 --> 14:48.721
until Harvey gets back.

14:48.787 --> 14:52.691
[laughter and cheering]

14:52.758 --> 14:53.926
- Agh.

14:53.993 --> 14:55.394
Who needs them?

14:55.461 --> 14:58.264
Okay, it's just me
and the clouds now.

14:58.330 --> 15:00.633
I'm just not gonna
think about Harvey.

15:00.699 --> 15:03.569
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:03.636 --> 15:06.005
Ahh, no, no, I refuse!

15:06.071 --> 15:08.507
You turn into something else,
please.

15:08.574 --> 15:11.377
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:11.443 --> 15:15.147
Still unsettling, but, you know,
much less emotional baggage.

15:15.214 --> 15:17.349
Ah, much better.

15:17.416 --> 15:19.551
[wind whistling]

15:19.618 --> 15:20.819
Ahh!

15:20.886 --> 15:24.256
No, begone, you terrible tease!

15:24.323 --> 15:28.294
[splashing]

15:28.360 --> 15:29.728
[squelch]

15:29.795 --> 15:30.929
- Help.

15:30.996 --> 15:34.466
- [laughing]
Yeah!

15:34.533 --> 15:36.935
- Uh, this isn't very fun.

15:37.002 --> 15:38.637
- Try throwing the mud.

15:38.704 --> 15:39.638
{\an3}- Okay.

15:39.705 --> 15:40.739
[grunts]
- Ah!

15:40.806 --> 15:42.041
- [grunts]
- Oof.

15:42.107 --> 15:44.543
- Ahh!
- Dog pile!

15:44.610 --> 15:46.845
all: [groaning]

15:46.912 --> 15:49.181
- All right, so I guess
we need a little Harvey.

15:49.248 --> 15:51.817
I mean, I thought everything
was going good.

15:51.884 --> 15:53.319
- No.
- No, definitely not.

15:53.385 --> 15:55.087
- Definitely not.
No, it's not good.

15:55.154 --> 15:57.222
It's not good!
- Hmm,

15:57.289 --> 16:01.093
if Harvey taught me one thing,
it's structure.

16:01.160 --> 16:05.431
Maybe we should use mud

16:05.497 --> 16:08.500
to build structures?

16:08.567 --> 16:10.803
I'm really kind of
reaching here, you guys.

16:10.869 --> 16:13.205
- Let's make a whole mud city!

16:13.272 --> 16:15.207
all: Yeah!

16:15.274 --> 16:18.344
[squelching]

16:18.410 --> 16:24.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:24.483 --> 16:25.918
- Ah, finally.

16:25.984 --> 16:29.021
The bad vibrations
can't reach me here.

16:29.088 --> 16:34.193
- [whistles]
Look at me hulking mad muscles!

16:34.259 --> 16:36.161
You likey?

16:36.228 --> 16:39.298
{\an1}Eh, Piri?
Eh, do you see 'em?

16:39.365 --> 16:40.933
[clinking]

16:40.999 --> 16:42.768
She'll come around.

16:42.835 --> 16:44.169
[squelch]

16:44.236 --> 16:45.804
- If anyone finds
any unbroken leaves,

16:45.871 --> 16:47.573
give 'em to me!

16:47.639 --> 16:51.677
{\an3}- Wow, Princess,
that's really impressive.

16:51.744 --> 16:53.479
- Oh, this little thing?

16:53.545 --> 16:55.481
I mean, I guess it's okay.

16:55.547 --> 16:58.684
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:58.751 --> 17:00.285
- Hey, Kratz.
- Hmm?

17:00.352 --> 17:02.154
Ahh, monster!

17:02.221 --> 17:03.789
{\an1}- We're the Fee
and Foo building.

17:03.856 --> 17:05.290
What are you making?

17:05.357 --> 17:07.992
- Oh, well, I couldn't think
of what to make,

17:08.060 --> 17:10.362
so I just decided
to dig a nap hole.

17:10.429 --> 17:12.830
And I'm gonna write
my name on this sign

17:12.897 --> 17:14.867
so everybody knows it's me.

17:14.933 --> 17:16.535
Good night.

17:16.602 --> 17:19.037
[snoring]

17:19.104 --> 17:20.539
- Have fun, Kratz.

17:20.606 --> 17:22.941
- I'm a walking building!

17:23.008 --> 17:24.510
- Oh, my gosh, Claire!

17:24.576 --> 17:27.445
- Oh, no, don't look!
It's not finished yet!

17:27.512 --> 17:30.249
- Please, let me see!

17:30.315 --> 17:33.285
- Well, okay, I guess you can
take a quick peek.

17:33.352 --> 17:36.855
Just remember
it's a work in progress.

17:36.922 --> 17:38.257
{\an3}- Gasp!

17:38.323 --> 17:41.393
His gaze is so powerful,
so wise!

17:41.460 --> 17:43.462
You have to share
your inspiration!

17:43.529 --> 17:47.499
- Well, Piri, let's just
call it a work of "heart."

17:47.566 --> 17:49.435
- [laughing]

17:49.501 --> 17:51.003
Oof!

17:51.069 --> 17:52.704
- I just--I gotta run.

17:52.771 --> 17:54.740
I just gotta run away
from all my problems.

17:54.807 --> 17:55.808
[grunting]

17:55.874 --> 17:57.342
[wind whistling]

17:57.409 --> 17:58.444
Harvey?

17:58.510 --> 18:00.913
- Hi, yes, I'm Horvey.
Hello!

18:00.979 --> 18:03.549
{\an1}- What?
No, I'm looking for Harvey.

18:03.615 --> 18:05.551
Harvey!
- [sighs]

18:05.617 --> 18:08.520
Nobody's ever looking
for ol' Horvey.

18:08.587 --> 18:12.591
- Well I guess this is it.
A life without Harvey.

18:12.658 --> 18:15.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:15.093 --> 18:17.529
It's darker
than I imagined.

18:17.596 --> 18:19.932
[exclaims]

18:19.998 --> 18:21.867
{\an3}Oh, hello.

18:21.934 --> 18:25.637
Oh, you look familiar.

18:25.704 --> 18:28.073
Very familiar.

18:28.140 --> 18:30.075
[squelching]

18:30.142 --> 18:31.109
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:31.176 --> 18:34.279
- This is mine now.

18:34.346 --> 18:35.948
This is also mine now.

18:36.014 --> 18:37.516
- Hey, give that back.

18:37.583 --> 18:40.085
- No, looks better on me!

18:40.152 --> 18:42.354
- You can't just take
other people's stuff!

18:42.421 --> 18:45.023
{\an1}- Uh-huh, and who's gonna
stop me?

18:45.090 --> 18:46.725
Harvey?
- [groans]

18:46.792 --> 18:49.695
{\an3}- Okay, okay,
I think I know Harvey best,

18:49.761 --> 18:53.031
{\an3}and I think I know exactly
how he'd handle this.

18:53.098 --> 18:55.400
Harvey would definitely,
definitely want you

18:55.467 --> 18:56.635
to punch it out.

18:56.702 --> 18:58.370
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.
[grunts]

18:58.437 --> 18:59.204
[squelch]

18:59.271 --> 19:00.739
- No problems here.

19:00.806 --> 19:02.608
{\an3}- ♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la ♪
[gasps]

19:02.674 --> 19:05.978
- Do you--Do you like
me muscles now?

19:06.044 --> 19:08.547
Do you?
You likey?

19:08.614 --> 19:09.982
- Uh, Claire?

19:10.048 --> 19:11.450
There's something
wrong with Rooter.

19:11.517 --> 19:13.051
{\an3}[gasps]
What are you doing?

19:13.118 --> 19:14.653
- I just can't get it right!

19:14.720 --> 19:17.256
{\an1}Do you know how hard it is
for imperfect hands

19:17.322 --> 19:19.458
to recreate perfection?

19:19.525 --> 19:20.592
Do you know?

19:20.659 --> 19:22.127
- Ahh!

19:22.194 --> 19:24.196
If Harvey was here,
he'd know what to do.

19:24.263 --> 19:26.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:26.498 --> 19:28.534
[squelch]

19:28.600 --> 19:30.936
[splattering]

19:31.003 --> 19:33.505
{\an3}- Foo?
What are you doing?

19:33.572 --> 19:35.173
- [growls]

19:35.240 --> 19:39.144
- Ahh, ahh,
I wish Harvey was here.

19:39.211 --> 19:41.013
all: [yelling]

19:41.079 --> 19:44.650
- Stop!
Hello, fellow kids.

19:44.716 --> 19:48.954
It is I, your friend,
Harvey Beaks!

19:49.021 --> 19:50.889
- Dade, what are you doing?

19:50.956 --> 19:54.493
- I'm not Dade!
I'm Harvey.

19:54.560 --> 19:57.195
Wow, see?
It really is Harvey!

19:57.262 --> 19:59.631
- Is Dade gonna kill us?

19:59.698 --> 20:01.333
- [grunting]

20:01.400 --> 20:03.969
So Harvey, uh, did you have
something you wanna say

20:04.036 --> 20:05.704
to everybody?

20:05.771 --> 20:10.042
Yes, you must all stop playing
in the mud like animals

20:10.108 --> 20:12.044
and return to your homes.

20:12.110 --> 20:15.213
Mud city is a filthy game,
and you should

20:15.280 --> 20:16.748
all listen to Dade.

20:16.815 --> 20:18.917
He is so smart and handsome--

20:18.984 --> 20:20.652
he could be a plus-sized model.

20:20.719 --> 20:23.121
- Hmph, he's a four at best.

20:23.188 --> 20:24.890
- Hey, don't argue with Harvey!

20:24.957 --> 20:26.358
- Give me that!
- No, no!

20:26.425 --> 20:28.360
You get away from him!
- Give it here!

20:28.427 --> 20:31.296
Um, actually, JK,
I was just kidding,

20:31.363 --> 20:33.732
so everyone ignore
everything I just said.

20:33.799 --> 20:36.268
I think Dade
smells like baby wipes.

20:36.335 --> 20:37.936
- [gasps]
I thought you liked

20:38.003 --> 20:39.471
my baby-fresh scent!

20:39.538 --> 20:41.873
{\an3}- Everyone should respect
Princess' art!

20:41.940 --> 20:43.208
And give her money!

20:43.275 --> 20:45.677
[laughs]
Hey!

20:45.744 --> 20:48.513
- I for one think that
big muscles are impressive

20:48.580 --> 20:51.350
and cool and that
it's okay to cry.

20:51.416 --> 20:55.187
- Foo has to marry Claire!
And kiss her 100 times!

20:55.253 --> 20:57.422
- We all need to leave
our bodies and ascend

20:57.489 --> 20:59.658
to another plane!
Ascend!

20:59.725 --> 21:01.326
[thud]

21:01.393 --> 21:06.531
all: [grunting]

21:06.598 --> 21:07.633
[squelch]

21:12.471 --> 21:15.007
- Whoa, that was weird.

21:15.073 --> 21:16.808
- What happened to us?

21:16.875 --> 21:18.810
- You guys went totally crazy.

21:18.877 --> 21:21.546
- You guys, we need to accept
that Harvey is gone,

21:21.613 --> 21:23.682
and he's not always gonna
be around to help us.

21:23.749 --> 21:25.884
- We can't always rely
on Harvey to tell us

21:25.951 --> 21:27.686
our muscles look good.

21:27.753 --> 21:30.756
We gotta believe in ourselves
that our muscles look good.

21:30.822 --> 21:34.292
- He's right--we're strong,
independent children.

21:34.359 --> 21:35.894
{\an1}- [sighs]
Maybe you guys

21:35.961 --> 21:37.663
are on to something.

21:37.729 --> 21:40.799
You know, maybe--maybe all we
needed is just each other.

21:40.866 --> 21:42.567
You know what?

21:42.634 --> 21:45.237
I think we're gonna be okay
after a--wait, what's that?

21:45.303 --> 21:46.838
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:46.905 --> 21:48.974
- Hey, everyone!
I'm back!

21:49.041 --> 21:50.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:50.108 --> 21:51.710
- Oh, thank Heavens!

21:51.777 --> 21:53.612
Get out of my way!
Harvey, Harvey, Harvey, Harvey!

21:53.679 --> 21:57.215
all: Harvey, Harvey, Harvey,
Harvey, Harvey, Harvey!

21:57.282 --> 21:59.184
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:59.251 --> 22:00.485
- What'd I miss?

22:01.853 --> 22:04.790
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:04.856 --> 22:11.897
<i>♪ ♪</i>
